ity by the vision of a crucifix between the antlers of the stag he was hunting."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705183,"age":2,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":12,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":22,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Eustace FitzStephen was born as the son of Stephen FitzHerbert and Wife of Stephen FitzHerbert. He had at least 1 son. He died after 1201, in Cavendish, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"–after 1201":"–pärast 1201","–1194":"–1194","–1201":"–1201","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","–1190":"–1190","–Female":"Surnud","1190":"1190","1106":"1106","after 1190":"pärast 1190","1201":"1201","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1150":"1150","1194":"1194","after 1201":"pärast 1201","Cavendish, Suffolk, England":"Cavendish, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"–after 1201":"–1201 jälkeen","–1194":"–1194","–1201":"–1201","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","–1190":"–1190","–Female":"Kuollut","1190":"1190","1106":"1106","after 1190":"1190 jälkeen","1201":"1201","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1150":"1150","1194":"1194","after 1201":"